 East London - The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that controlled blasting scheduled for Monday has been cancelled and is scheduled to take place on Tuesday, 6 August, on the R72 Section 3 (KM 49.24) to Section 4 (KM 16.0) between Birah River and Openshaw Village, from 3pm until 5pm. The road will be closed between Gcinisa Village and Hamburg turn off. “Motorists are asked to use the road with caution,” Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region Manager said. SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  